article.description: Nisre Zouzoua scored 19 of his career-high 30 points in the second half on Tuesday night to help Bryant beat Louisiana-Monroe 64-57 in the consolation game of the Legends Classic's Sub-Regional.
article.headline: Zouzoua's career-high 30 leads Bryant past ULM, 64-57
article.linkText: Zouzoua's career-high 30 leads Bryant past ULM, 64-57
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Nisre Zouzoua scored 19 of his career-high 30 points in the second half on Tuesday night to help Bryant beat Louisiana-Monroe 64-57 in the consolation game of the Legends Classic's Sub-Regional. Zouzoua made 13 of 22 from the field for his third-straight game with 20-plus points Sam McDaniel's 3-pointer with 15:57 to play gave ULM (1-4) its biggest lead, 37-30. But Zouzoua hit two 3s and scored 12 points during a 26-10 spurt that gave the Bulldogs a nine-point lead with 6 minutes remaining. Bryant (2-3) shot 59 percent (16 of 27) in the second half, and finished with a season-low seven turnovers. McDaniel led the Warhawks with 17 points and nine rebounds while Travis Munnings scored 10 with eight boards. ULM made 24 of 63 (38 percent) from the field, including 7 of 25 (28 percent) from 3-point range.
